  "sortnum": 1,
  "pages": [
    {
      "type": "text",
      "text": "By engraving gold into the blocks, they can disperse the soul tears in a slightly safer manner.$(br) I will need to make a proper structure out of this, something to contain the soul tears without being solid. Some kind of soul cage perhaps?"
    },
    {
      "type": "lacrimis:infusion",
      "recipe": "lacrimis:infusion/rune_tier1",
      "text": "Eight seems like a very good number for this."
    },
    {
      "type": "text",
      "text": "While these blocks will not accept tears from an outside source, it is pretty simple to fix that.$(br)These duct connectors can be used to provide the soul cage with the tears it needs. They could also carry things through the tears out of the cage? That sounds a bit hazardous though."
    },
    {
      "type": "crafting",
      "recipe": "lacrimis:crafting/rune_duct1",
      "text": "Make sure to include one in every soul cage. No more than that, as it is hard to control the flow as it is."
    },
    {
      "type": "text",
      "text": "This soul cage uses seven tier I runes, and a tier I duct connector. It also requires sixteen valid cage blocks, any combination of the following: $(li)Iron Bars$(li)Chains$(li)End rods$(br2)Activate it with redstone or a $(l:basics/divining_rod)Divining Rod$(/l)."
    },
